    <h1>Privacy Notice</h1>
    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 19 June 2025</p>
    <p>This Privacy Notice applies to the use of the XLedger Client Invoice Portal.</p>

    <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
    <p>This portal is operated by <strong>XLedger Ltd</strong>, a service provider offering invoice and legal services tracking tools for law firms.</p>
    <p><strong>Platform Operator (Data Processor):</strong><br/>
    XLedger Ltd<br/>
    Registered in England and Wales<br/>
    Contact: <a href="mailto:privacy@xledger.co.uk">privacy@xledger.co.uk</a></p>

    <p><strong>Law Firm (Data Controller):</strong><br/>
    [Law Firm Name]<br/>
    Lawyer: Jane Smith<br/>
    Contact: lawfirm@domain.co.uk</p>

    <h2>2. What Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Client names and contact details</li>
      <li>Invoice numbers, service details, and costs</li>
      <li>Payment information (for processing only)</li>
      <li>Login credentials (usernames, encrypted passwords)</li>
      <li>Access logs, IP address, and browser metadata</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To display invoices for legal services</li>
      <li>To process payments securely</li>
      <li>To maintain client records in compliance with regulations</li>
      <li>To protect portal security and integrity</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Payment Data & PCI-DSS Compliance</h2>
    <p>Payments through this portal are processed by third-party, PCI-DSS compliant payment gateways (e.g., Stripe). XLedger does <strong>not store</strong> full card numbers or CVV codes.</p>
    <p>Payment data is encrypted and transmitted securely via SSL/TLS to the processor. Only transaction status (success/failure) is retained by us for record purposes.</p>

    <h2>5. User Account and Password Security</h2>
    <p>Registered users must use secure passwords. All passwords are hashed and encrypted. We recommend not sharing login credentials. Suspicious activity may result in temporary lockout.</p>

    <h2>6. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Contractual obligation (e.g., invoice delivery)</li>
      <li>Legal obligation (e.g., tax or regulatory)</li>
      <li>Legitimate interest (e.g., fraud prevention)</li>
      <li>Consent (if applicable for communications)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Who We Share Data With</h2>
    <p>Your data may be shared with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your instructed law firm</li>
      <li>Our hosting and payment service providers</li>
      <li>Regulators or authorities if legally required</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Data Storage & Retention</h2>
    <p>Data is stored in the UK or EEA. We retain invoice and legal service data for a minimum of 6 years as required by law. Inactive login data may be deleted after 12 months.</p>

    <h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access a copy of your data</li>
      <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
      <li>Request deletion (where applicable)</li>
      <li>Restrict or object to processing</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent (if previously given)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise your rights, email: <a href="mailto:privacy@xledger.co.uk">privacy@xledger.co.uk</a></p>

    <h2>10. Cookies</h2>
    <p>We only use essential cookies for session authentication and login management. No third-party tracking or analytics cookies are used.</p>

    <h2>11. International Transfers</h2>
    <p>If data is transferred outside the UK or EEA, we use appropriate safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses and encryption measures to protect your data.</p>

    <h2>12. Complaints</h2>
    <p>If you believe your data rights have been violated, you may contact the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO):<br/>
    <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank">https://ico.org.uk</a> or call 0303 123 1113.</p>

    <h2>13. Updates</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Notice from time to time. The latest version will always be available on this page with the effective date indicated.</p>

